The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Tanishq eyes 

 40% sales rise

 -Titan thrust on store expansion, brand promotions 

 SOHINI MOOKHERJEA 

Calcutta, 

 June 24: Jewellery brand Tanishq expects to maintain 

 its growth rate at over 40 per cent in the current fiscal. 

 The jewellery market in India is estimated at around Rs 65,000 crore and the branded segment accounts for Rs 20,000 crore. The share of branded jewellery is expected to double in the next two years.

 We had a turnover of Rs 1,250 crore in 2006-07 compared with Rs 732 crore in the previous fiscal. We expect to maintain the growth momentum this fiscal, said V. Govindraj, vice-president, retail and marketing, Tanishq. 

 Tanishq retails its products in the Gulf and the Far East. It is now planning to launch its brand in the US. The company looks to increase its stores to 110 by the end of this fiscal from 88 at present.

 Tanishq has 12 format stores in the city, spread across 3,000 to 10,000 sq ft. It recently launched a concept store at the Fort Knox jewellery mall. It plans to open five or six more stores this year. 

 The diamond jewellery business grew 26 per cent last year. Exports make up for around 10 per cent of the branded jewellery divisions turnover. The factory at Hosur in Tamil Nadu provides crafted jewellery for the domestic and international markets. 

 Parent company Titan Industries Ltd was set up in 1984 as a joint venture between the Tata Group and the Tamil Nadu Industrial Development Corporation. 

 It diversified into the jewellery business in 1995.




